Armed men have abducted the wife and daughters of a traditional ruler in Odigbo Local Government Area of Ondo State. The victim, wife of the Orunja of Odigbo, Oba Rufus Akinrimade, was abducted alongsidetwoof herdaughtersaswellastheirdriver. The incident occurred when they monarch’s family members were travelling on the Owo-Oba-Ikare Akoko Road to Akungba- Akoko to check on one of the children who a student of Adekunle Ajasin University, Akungba-Akoko (AAUA). A palace source disclosed that the kidnappers had demanded N100 million to free the victims. The source said abductors had contacted the palace and had not shifted grounds in their negotiations. According to the source, the kidnappers have been negotiating directly with the traditional ruler. The monarch, Oba Akinrimade, also confirmed the kidnap of his wife and the two daughters alongside the driver. He listed the names of the victims Queen Regina Akinrinmade (wife), Precious and Mercy Akinrinmade (daughters) and the driver, identified simply as Mr. Lateef. The monarch appealed to well-meaning Nigerians, security operatives to help rescue the victims. According to him, the abductees have spent four days in the kidnappers’ den. The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Mr. Femi Joseph, said the three members of a family and their driver were reported to have been kidnapped on Oba Akoko Road. He said the command had begun investigation into the incident with an assurance to rescue them unhurt. Joseph said the command had noticed the recent developments in the area and had restrategised to chase away the criminals from the area. Meanwhile, the Minority Leader of Ondo State House of Assembly, Hon Rasheed Elegbeleye, who narrowly escaped from being kidnapped on the route, narrated how the gunmen shot at his car in an attempt to stop him.